🔹 NFS (Network File System)
✅ Definition
Shared storage over network
Multiple pods can access same data
🔹 Key Idea
One storage → many pods
Data stored outside node
🔹 Flow
Pod → PVC → PV → NFS Server → Storage
🔹 Features
Supports ReadWriteMany (RWX)
Data persists
Works across multiple nodes
🔹 Use Cases
Shared storage (multiple pods)
File storage (images, docs)
Logs storage
Multi-node applications
🔹 Advantage
Same data accessible from all pods
🔹 Limitation
Network dependency
Slightly slower than local disk
