🔹 1. How PV binds with PVC?

👉 Binding happens based on matching conditions

✅ Conditions checked:
Storage size (e.g., 1Gi)
Access mode (ReadWriteOnce, ReadWriteMany)
StorageClass (if specified)

🔹 2. Components involved in binding

👉 These components work together:

Component	         Role
PV	              Actual storage
PVC	           Request
StorageClass	  Defines type (for dynamic)
Kubernetes       Controller	Matches & binds
CSI Driver	     Creates PV (dynamic case)

🔹 3. How external storage comes into cluster (PV role)

👉 PV acts as a bridge to external storage

🔹 Example (NFS)
nfs:
  server: 192.168.1.100
  path: /nfs-data

👉 What happens:

External Storage (NFS / AWS Disk)
        ↓
PV (represents it in K8s)
        ↓
Cluster can now use it

👉 PV = representation of external storage inside cluster

